  {link: "https://www.bespokepost.com/careers#", title: "Lead Developer", full_text: "Check out the Valentine's Day store and de-stress your February Boxes Products All This Just In Food Style & Grooming Drink Gear & Den Boxes Esquire The Post Give A Gift Join The Club Join The Club Club Shipment Club Shipment No shipment this month {{(box_cart.line_items | box_line_items)[0].name}} &plus; Club Shipment {{line_item.name}} With {{line_item.child.name}} Recipient: {{line_item.recipient_name}} Quantity {{line_item.quantity}} {{line_item.subtotal + line_item.child.subtotal | currency_cents }} {{moreItems(box_cart.line_items)}} View Cart Cart Your cart is currently empty {{line_item.name}} With {{line_item.child.name}} Recipient: {{line_item.recipient_name}} Quantity {{line_item.quantity}} {{line_item.subtotal + line_item.child.subtotal | currency_cents }} {{moreItems(cart.line_items)}} Total {{cart.subtotal | currency_cents}} Checkout Account Profile Preferences Shipping Billing Order History Invite Friends, Earn $25 Sign out Sign out Register Sign in Your Credit Card was declined. Please add a new credit card or we cannot ship you further boxes. Careers About Bespoke Post We’re changing how men discover and purchase products online. You’ll work with a small, smart, and nimble team - and have an immediate impact on our growing company. Some benefits include: Competitive salary Owning a piece of the company through equity Fortune - 500 caliber health & dental Flexible vacation Flexible working schedule Free lunches Happy hours, retreats, and other activities Monthly taste tests of the latest beers, wines and treats New office space with snacks and more (coming soon) Open Positions Senior Marketing Associate Merchandising Lead Operations & Customer Service Associate Lead Developer Designer To apply, email your resume and any other relevant info (portfolio, GitHub account, etc.) to jobs@bespokepost.com Senior Marketing Associate Help build our marketing team into a well-oiled, customer-generating machine. You will work directly with the head of marketing to mold all lead generation, customer acquisition and customer retention activities. The job will be a blissful union of deep quantitative analysis and creative, idea-generating exercises (often taking place at local watering holes). You... Can take a quantitative deep-dive into specific marketing channels, identifying opportunities to optimize and improve performance Are comfortable developing, implementing and managing a comprehensive retargeting program working closely with third-party vendors Will optimize our ongoing email and customer contact strategy Work well with various groups, including as the creative, engineering and merchandising departments Adhere to a simple philosophy: test, test, and tests Can manage ongoing campaign tracking and reporting across all channels Write the occasional piece of copy, resize the occasional image, and code an email or two Your goals are to... Develop a comprehensive marketing metrics dashboard Improve conversion on an existing marketing channel by 5% Develop 1 new successful customer acquisition channel per quarter The ideal person... Has 1–3 years work experience in management consulting, investment banking, or similar field Has experience in or knowledge of marketing Is both analytical and creative. Can not only can get the right data, but then derive actionable insights and implement creative solutions from it Is a self-starter who takes initiative So detail-oriented you already found the typo in this job description Is the equivalent of an excel Navy seal Back to top Merchandising Lead We’re looking for a creative and energetic person with merchandising experience to build out our product and brand portfolio. You’ll be responsible for the Products section of our business, building a new “storefront” each month that fits a cross-site theme. You… Should have a keen eye for products our customers will love Always have ideas for new products and experiences to try out. Your friends go to you when looking for recommendations. Will build relationships and negotiate with existing and new partners Want to grow over time, taking on new responsibly and roles Your goals are to... Build a new “storefront” each month Buy at least 50 products per month Maintain existing relationships with our partners Identify and build relationships with new partners The ideal person… Has merchandising experience in a prior role Has a strong resume that shows you’re ready to take on lots of new responsibility Want to really impress us? Send us images, descriptions and prices of 3 products that you think our customers would love. Explain why they would love them. Figure out how to email us directly. If you’re not up for the challenge, simply email jobs@bespokepost.com Back to top Operations & Customer Service Associate We're looking for an energetic and detailed-oriented individual who wants to join a fast-growing commerce company at the ground level. You'll have direct ownership of the business operations and relationship with our warehouse in Louisville, You’ll be helping to manage our customer service channels (phone, email, and social networks). You… Will own the day-to-day relationship with our off-site warehouse to make sure outbound logistics are running like clockwork. Should be comfortable with your quantitative skills. Experience with Excel is required; experience with SQL is a plus. If you don’t have the latter, you should be comfortable learning it very quickly. Will be obsessed with making sure all orders placed are accurately fulfilled each day Can think on your feet and are willing to do whatever it takes to make things right for our customers when things go wrong. Should be comfortable talking with customers and bringing your personality into the fold. We’re not going for robotic responses. Want to grow over time, taking on new responsibilities and roles. Will own key reporting metrics, working to support multiple functions as needed Are ready and willing to work hard as we build up our company Your goals are to… Help bring our response times to customers to less than 1 hour during business hours, and less than 1 day during non-business hours / weekends. Manage off-site warehouse to ensure they are meeting Service Level Agreement (SLA) targets for fulfillment Co-lead at least one initiative per month to automate activities related to customer service and operations. The ideal person… Is a recent college grad with 1-2 years experience in an analytical role Has relevant experience organizing and executing something. We want to see some concrete examples of what you're made of (and what you can make). Has a strong resume that shows you’re ready to take on lots of new responsibility. Back to top Lead Developer Are you an experienced Ruby Developer ready to take your skills to the next level? Do you appreciate style and craftsmanship? You'll have the chance to own the technical direction of the company and have a significant impact on our growth. You... Have experience building and managing complex applications Have experience working with and designing APIs Test and measure results to improve the user experience Enjoy working with cross functional teams such as marketing and design to improve key metrics across the business Are curious and interested in pursuing anything cool you can think of (seriously, we are open to good ideas) Your goals are to... Figure out how to leverage our extensive user data to build a better, more personalized experience for consumers Build a new level of interaction with AngularJS or other JS frameworks Introduce user generated content to help create a community Enhance the existing foundation that we've already built The ideal person... Has advanced knowledge of Ruby, Rails, HTML, and software design principles Has basic knowledge of SQL, JavaScript, CSS, unit testing Is experienced with some of our tools: AngularJS, Heroku, git, postgresql, rspec Back to top Designer Job Description As a Designer, you’ll be working within our creative team, touching all aspects of the business. We’re looking for someone who wants to develop his or her skills and make a mark. You’ll be involved with our website, product packaging, marketing assets, and more. You... Have a strong sense of brand-specific design Can design and code responsive HTML email templates Are quick at editing product photos Can design new and/or edit existing web pages Can create images and graphics for assets across the company Have an interest shaping user experience within men’s ecommerce Your goals are to... Design and support marketing & merchandising initiatives such as advertisements and contests Figure out how to improve site metrics such as conversions, time on site, etc. Create something new once a quarter. Propose it and build it – user generated content, improved packaging, etc. – we want you to push the company forward The ideal person... Has a degree in graphic or interaction design Built an online portfolio with print and web design work examples Has 1-3 yrs of design work experience Understands typography and composition Has excellent knowledge of Adobe Illustrator, InDesign, and Photoshop Is proficient with HTML5/CSS3 Drop us a line at jobs@bespokepost.com Back to top About Bespoke We scour the world for time-tested, small-batch, or otherwise remarkable gear. Check out our theme-driven boxes, choice products, and the stories behind it all. Spread the Word If you like what we do, tell your friends. For every one who joins the club, you get $25. That's what we call a win-win. Get In Touch Give us a shout at 888.565.6762 or e-mail us at help@bespokepost.com. We’ve got your back. Twitter Facebook Boxes Products Archive The Post Redeem a Gift Buy a Gift Contact Careers FAQ Legal 72 Allen Street, 3rd floor New York, NY, 10002 ©2013 nabfly, Inc. Made in NYC Forgot password? Email Sign in Email Password {{ login_errors }} Forgot your password? 