s / feature enhancement requests, and tracking issues to resolution Managing defects and proactively escalating risks to management and key stakeholders Evaluating, recommending, and implementing software to automate and optimize new and existing business processes Training and mentoring team members on testing methodologies Requirements: B.S. degree or foreign academic equivalent in General Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or a related engineering field 1 to 3 years of prior software testing experience Experience using test automation tools is a plus Thorough understanding of the software development life cycle Excellent problem solving and analytical skills Professional and/or academic background in SQL and relational database concepts A drive to learn quickly and constantly adapt to new challenges Able to think creatively about global solutions to testing challenges Must be very detail-oriented with regards to testing Excellent written and verbal communication skills General understanding of financial concepts Strong self-motivation, and the ability to work effectively with limited guidance when necessary Apply: Please submit your cover letter and resume to WorkWithUs@Sociocast.com with “Quality Assurance Engineer” in the subject of your email. read moreread less Data Scientist, R&D / New York City Uses predictive modeling, statistics, trend analysis, and other data analysis techniques to collect, explore and identify the right data to be analyzed from internal and external sources, then constructs software systems and algorithms to explain or predict customer behavior and solve a variety of business problems. Assists business analysts with finding patterns and relationships in data. Builds predictive models using data, tests the model on results outside of the sample size and verifies the model in the real world. Sociocast is hiring a Data Scientist to help build out an industry-leading Big Data company with world-class operational systems 