  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/mongodb-uiux-summer-intern", title: "MongoDB UI/UX Summer Intern", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions MongoDB UI/UX Summer Intern New York, NY MongoDB is seeking an interaction experience intern to focus on user interface development for our online products and services. You will be responsible for UI design and implementation for mongodb.org, the MongoDB Monitoring Service (MMS) and other products and services we develop, and serving as an advocate for users of these products throughout the design and development process. Responsibilities Help define and implement user experience for MongoDB related online products and services Develop a deep understanding of users through ongoing research and analysis of user behavior patterns, advocate for the user Collaborate with MongoDB Engineering to research, design and develop user interfaces for MongoDB products and services, partnering with engineers for design and implementation Assist our software engineering interns in making their \"backend\" projects more beautiful and user friendly Requirements BA/BS in human/computer interaction and/or interaction design or 1-3 years’ relevant work experience Skills and experience prototyping, designing, testing, implementing, and evaluating user experience for web based applications Familiarity with usability heuristics and best practices in UX design Ability to create wireframes and processflow diagrams, strong wireframe and user testing skills Ability to plan and administer usability tests Strong portfolio of visual design examples Strong experience with HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript Experience working with version control systems, specifically git Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading NoSQL database. Designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable. MongoDB enables new types of applications, better customer experience, faster time to market and lower costs. MongoDB has a thriving global community with more than 6 million downloads, 125,000 Online Education registrations, 25,000 MongoDB User Group (MUG) members and 20,000 annual MongoDB Days attendees. The company has more than 900 customers, including many of the world’s largest organizations. To all recruitment agencies: MongoDB does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias or MongoDB employees. MongoDB is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Life @ MongoDB 1 2 Did You Know? You can apply for a job using your LinkedIn account! Save time and include added resources by using LinkedIn to include your resume, work experience, and recommendations in your application. Apply Now With LinkedIn Apply now in New York, NY Copyright © 2014 MongoDB, Inc. Legal Notices Information you submit as part of your application is subject to the MongoDB Jobs Privacy Policy", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, key_skill_one: "HCJ", key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil},
  {link: "http://augmate.com/careers.html", title: "CTO", full_text: "Home Tour About News Careers Contact MENU Join us as we explore a new frontier h1 { color:#74838c;} We are looking for specific individuals that can help us to build a new and improved workplace environment. As a wearable first company, we are looking for futurists, with a passion for optimizing the way things are, the vision to see the way things should be, and the ability to build that future now. Augmate is building a development platform that will allow us to produce agile and scalable digital eyewear applications to improve the way deskless workers perform in the field. We are looking for entrepreneurial individuals that can help design this solution and capitalize on this tremendous opportunity we have in front of us. CTO At this early stage, you must have the expertise to architect and engineer our core platform. There is quite a bit of work ahead. You will be an intricate part of developing our wearable first engineering culture and the team that will lay the foundation for the future of the industry. You will assist in determining the optimal technologies that will allow us to scale with our customers and evolve rapidly as this technology advances. You should have experience with developing enterprise software in cloud-based environment, a strong understanding of how to best leverage third-party API’s, and experience developing a secure platform that facilitates performance utilizing real-time information in a workplace. Above all else, you must be a passionate coder that genuinely enjoys to build. We are looking for a leader. We would like this leader to effectively communicate our vision, not only to the members of our team, but to the partners and customers we are working with. You should be comfortable as a recognized thought leader in the space, as we pave the way for wearable technology to impact the workplace. If you have had experience working on software that has been implemented into a large industrial environment, well that’s a big plus in our book. Apply Apply ENTERPRISE SOFTWARE ENGINEER As part of the foundational team, your role is crucial. You will be developing Augmate’s ability to connect with outside enterprise databases (i.e. SAP) and engineer the infrastructure that will ultimately manage, deliver, and display data that will change the way workers interact with their environment. You must have experience working in large enterprise environments, engineering ERP systems, manipulating large amounts of data, working with third-party API’s, and optimizing solutions in a rapidly evolving cloud-based environment. You will be leading the design, development, and testing of features/functions delivered via platform components and/or services that are highly scalable, available and reliable. Apply Apply LEAD ANDROID DEVELOPER We are building software on the platform of the future. It just so happens, most of these digital eyewear platforms are running Android SDK. Our Lead Android Developer, as part of our foundational team, will be instrumental in developing industry leading digital eyewear applications for the deskless workplace. We are looking for someone who is passionate about building scalable and agile applications, with development experience in enterprise software API and cloudbase applications. You will be focused on user interface design and integration with revolutionary new hardware. You will be working to optimize our solutions to leverage sensors and gesture driven interfaces. Knowledge of computer vision would be a plus. Apply Apply WEARABLE ENGINEER In order to really maximize the capabilities of our software we have to optimize our the capabilities of hardware we’re working with. Incredible attention to sensors and their mechanics will improve the way we understand and are able to deal with the spatial requirements of deskless work environments. You will be crucial to our operations, working closely with the user experience team, as we work with our various hardware partners to provide actionable enhancements to both their capabilities and ours. As our main area of concern is with Augmented Reality, a keen understanding of OpenCV is desired. Experience with various embedded systems and hardware technologies like Bluetooth and Wifi are a plus. Ultimately, we are looking for someone who dreams about wearable technologies and desires to be at the forefront of their physical development. Apply Apply API DEVELOPER As API Developer. you’ll be building out crucial connections to various online services in order to lay the groundwork for a robust end-user experience. You’ll be partnering with internal teams to ensure that AUGMATE maintains the optimal API strategies, standards and best practices as well as collaborating with product owners to develop both private and public APIs. To that end you should be proficient in various protocols and data formats, including REST, JSON with expertise in security, including OAuth and SSL. Apply Apply DEVELOPMENT INTERN You’re a hacker -- a digital enthusiast with an entrepreneurial streak who is ready to join a small start up. You piece together existing technologies and are incredibly excited about the future of wearable technologies and augmented reality. As Development Intern, you’ll be on the ground floor of a fast growing startup developing the foundations of digital eyewear applications. Your experience with various coding platforms allow you to quickly piece together physical and application prototypes. We’re looking for someone with an insatiable desire to be even better. Apply Apply BUSINESS OPERATIONS & MARKETING INTERN In this highly diversified role, you'll assist in expanding the Augmate business in all directions. You will be working on the operations and marketing side of a leading software development startup, on a cutting edge technological platform, digital eyewear and wearables. We're looking for someone with some serious business, analytical, and social media savvy, a keen ability to understand the potential of this market and our brand, -and an interest in being at the intersection of hardware and software. Along with strong organization skills, a keen ability for strategy and aggressive implementation, you must have great communication skills and be able to build out our content strategy. You will be placed directly at the forefront of this new technological frontier and be directly involved with the growth of not only Augmate, but the industry as a whole. Apply Apply UI / UX DESIGN INTERN As a UI/UX Design Intern at Augmate, you will work closely with engineers and the business team throughout all stages of the product cycle. We are looking for a critical thinker with great design sense, a strong technical background, and an eye for making things better. This is an opportunity to create the standard for how the world will interact with digital eyewear technologies that display field-of-view information in the near future. As an ideal candidate, your skills in Adobe’s Creative Suite as well as HTML and CSS make you a great communicator, able to quickly prototype ideas. We’re looking for an out of the box thinker who understands 3D space and is not afraid to challenge the way things are and propose the way things should or can be. 3D Modeling experience in Sketchup, Rhino, 3DSMax, or Maya is a plus. Apply Apply Home Tour About News CareersBack to Top 📞 1-885-AUGMATE Copyright © 2013 AUGMATE.COM All rights reserved.    ✉ INFO@AUGMATE.COM TERMS OF SERVICE | PRIVACY POLICY", is_draft: true, company_id: 83, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 10, key_skill_one: nil, key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Executive", description: nil},
