  {link: "http://artsicle.hiretracking.com/artsicle/job/61", title: "Engineering Intern", full_text: "| job openings (view all) http://www.artiscle.com/ engineering intern artsicle is hiring summer interns! love art? ready to join one of the fastest growing startups in nyc? want to have some fun with your internship? if so, keep reading! artsicle interns will learn about startup life, tech, the art world, and what it means to build something. you'll be exposed to a ton of other great startups, mentors, investors. you'll visit artist's studios, stop by gallery openings, and help build something world changing. you can build new skills and develop a portfolio of real work. and we think you'll have fun, too. you'll have a very flexible schedule and can often work from anywhere (minimum of 20 hours/wk). and hey, if we all get along, we might just ask you to stick around fulltime. check out the description below and apply! here at artsicle, we believe in getting our hands dirty across the full stack, from the css to our ec2 servers. artsicle's cto is a self-taught developer - so don't worry about not having a cs degree. however, what comes with being self-taught is not to fearing the unknown and knowing how to jump in and learn just about anything. artsicle is looking for self motivated developers who don't cringe at the thought of stepping outside their comfort zone, or the idea of taking a customer support call. artsicle is a small team and it's very likely that you'll do everything from wire a piece of art to tweak our recommendation algorithm - it's a great way to become a jack of all trades. if you believe in learning new skills while excelling at your current ones, then artsicle is the place for you. our stack - mysql, redis, memcached, linux, ruby, rails, and front end stuffs (html, css, js/coffeescript) requirements: html & css - if you don't know html & css, start learning here. a strong understanding is quick and invaluable. http://learn.shayhowe.com/html-css programming language - we don't care what language but proficiency in one will help you learn another. keen eye for design - you care that that font is 24px, not 23px. strong writing & communication - clear writing skills and a confident opinion will help you communicate with the team. start-up attitude - we're passionate about what we do, and we want you to be too. get it done - you feel comfortable doing things, even when no one is telling you exactly what to do. great to have: interested in - going deep in javascript, the good parts of course. knowledge of coffeescript is even better. git - or subversion, mercurial etc. twitter bootstrap - it makes communication and responsiveness a lot easier. sass - a great superset of css a bit of photoshop knowledge always helps if you don't meet the above criteria yet, here are a few steps to help you get there: learn to program - a fantastic get started book. http://pragprog.com/book/ltp2/learn-to-program rails tutorial - not only do you build twitter but you learn some up to date techniques such as tdd. http://www.railstutorial.com build something (anything), push it to the world and tell us about it. share this position: share in twitter share in facebook apply required fields are marked as (*) first name (*) last name (*) email (*) resume location personal website what have you built? (programmed or otherwise) (*) what do you love about artsicle? (*) github (link) tell us about ways you've sought self improvement. (*) powered by hiretracking", is_draft: true, company_id: 72, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, key_skill_one: nil, key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil},
  {link: "https://www.biodigitalhuman.com/home/jobs.html#collapseOne", title: "Senior Web Developer", full_text: "sign up log in sign out email password remember me forgot password? or 3rd party login facebook google features pricing jobs we want to improve the way people understand their health. we have a diverse team of software engineers, 3d animators, graphic artists, and scientists - who all share a passion for technology and healthcare. we're determined to transform the way people communicate about their health, starting with how they learn about the human body. join our team if you'd like to work in a fast-paced, dynamic startup environment be a part of cutting-edge 3d technology in the health and wellness space meet smart, interesting, and creative people dedicated to improving healthcare and patient literacy share a workspace in the heart of soho, manhattan! job listings senior web developer biodigital, an established nyc-based digital health company, is seeking an extremely talented web application developer to help build its latest flagship product, a cutting-edge 3d web application (www.biodigitalhuman.com). the ideal candidate has intimate knowledge of the latest web technologies and a strong desire to build a high-quality, scalable web app that will revolutionize the health and medical sectors. the successful candidate thrives in a fast-paced start-up environment, but seeks to join a fun, proven company headquartered in the heart of soho. qualifications degree in computer science or software engineering, or equivalent experience at least 3 years’ programming experience experience with python, java, perl, javascript, html 5, css, mysql or similar technology passion for working at the intersection of technology and health, and desire to build a cutting-edge health visualization platform interest in the latest state-of-the-art programming technologies highly motivated, independent, and hungry to succeed strong communication skills knowledge of opengl, webgl, or other 3d programming experience a plus for an outstanding programmer, this is an opportunity to lead and learn at a company driving radical changes in healthcare. the hire will report directly to senior management. competitive compensation, excellent benefits. and the opportunity to get in early on a company whose potential has already been proven. submit resume to recruiter@biodigital.com. the company biodigital is a biomedical visualization company that is revolutionizing the way people understand their health and the human body. its latest product, the biodigital human, is a comprehensive 3d human body accessible through the web. the human platform allows users to learn about anatomy, disease, and treatments in a manner that resembles life itself. the platform has already received tremendous accolades, including #1 education app in the google chrome web store, winner of nvidia’s one to watch award at the 2012 emerging companies summit, featured presenter at tedmed 2012, and one of .net magazine’s 20 best 3d websites of 2011. the tight-knit team of engineers, 3d animators, scientists, and entrepreneurs are passionately working to solve real-world problems. contact us faq biodigital blog jobs terms of service privacy policy © 2013 biodigital, inc. humanely made in nyc. all rights reserved.", is_draft: true, company_id: 108, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, key_skill_one: "Python", key_skill_two: "Java", sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil},
  {link: "http://songza.com/page/careers/", title: "Android Development Lead", full_text: "Songza Search: Sign up Log in Music Concierge Popular Browse All Careers at Songza The only thing more awesome than listening to great music from Songza is being part of the team that makes Songza tick. We’re passionate about building products that are useful, simple, and delightful. Songza is a lifestyle enhancement service. Our goal is to make the things our users do every day better. Our free streaming music service has expert-made playlists for every occasion and makes it outrageously easy to find the right one, at the right time. Songza is one of the most exciting startups in NYC. We’ve been named among the Top 10 Most Innovative Companies in Music by Fast Company, an Editors’ Choice app by Apple, Google Play and PC Mag, as well as an ‘App Store Best of 2012’ by Apple. In July 2013, Mayor Michael Bloomberg presented us with a New York City Neighborhood Achievement Award . We’ve been covered by the New York Times, Wall Street Journal, CNN, TechCrunch, and Mashable. Most importantly, we delight millions of users like these: The Songza app is like your much cooler friend who always has the perfect song for every moment. @OliviaWilde Songza is making my workday so much better right now. @_DrunkBlonde @Songza officially makes mornings 1000x better.‏@allisonplove Songza makes running so much more enjoyable. @nixhaley So @alfredoflores just showed me @songza for workout playlists. Why didn't any of my 26 million best friends show me this? #whichplaylist. @JustinBieber Starting to think Songza is better than a boyfriend. It knows exactly how to make me happy. @perfectcompanyy Falling to sleep: Songza. Waking up: Songza. Working out: Songza. My life is forever changed. @JonUchacz Songza is in the Long Island City neighborhood of New York City. We’re one subway stop from Grand Central Station and you can practically spit into the East River from our office. Besides a breathtaking view of the Manhattan skyline, Long Island City has great food options and good neighborhood bars. Our office is a funky, open, industrial space, and will never be featured in the Herman Miller catalog. Over the last 7 years, our team have become expert and highly regarded players in a complex media landscape -- prior to Songza, we founded AmieStreet.com and sold the brand and customer base to Amazon in 2010. Songza’s fast growth, high app ratings and word-of-mouth buzz has us poised for a fun, successful 2013. We work hard. We play music all day. We high five when awesome things happen. We love what we do. Available Positions Android Development Lead iOS Engineer Infrastructure-ish Engineeer Editorial Internship Regional Sales Manager Yield Optimization Manager Account Manager Other Positions Editorial Internship Songza is looking for an enthusiastic and motivated intern to do music research and make amazing long-form playlists. You’ll also be brainstorming activities to soundtrack and updating existing playlists, all while listening to great music. A successful candidate will be a team player who is obsessed with music and interested in expert-level music curation. Seriously, music should be your favorite thing and you should know a lot about it. You should also be intensely curious about the artists, genres, eras, etc. that you know nothing about. This editorial position is ideal for a college student who wants to make playlists that will delight Songza's users and expose them to great music, and who wants to learn more about the fast-paced and quickly-evolving music industry in the context of a startup company. Applicants should be willing to commit at least 12-18 hours per week at our Long Island City office. We will work with you to create a weekly schedule that accommodates your school and work commitments. We are recruiting interns for spring and summer internships, that run from the end of January to mid-June, and from June to the end of August. Salary: A $1000 stipend given in two parts at the middle and end of your internship. Requirements: High school degree Advanced knowledge of recorded music (preferably across several genres) Strong Internet research skills, particularly with regard to music Ability to multitask and meet deadlines under pressure Be available a minimum of 2-3 days per week in the office, from 11 a.m.- 5 p.m. A great personality Bonus Points: Experience writing about music (please include writing samples in your application if you have them) Experience copy editing Enrolled in a 2-4 year accredited U.S. college or university and eligible to receive credit or have an academic letter of support for your internship Basic knowledge of the digital music space Please send your resume, cover letter, and writing samples to internships@songza.com. Infrastructure-ish Engineer Songza is seeking an experienced infrastructure-ish engineer to ride herd over our prodution systems and infrastructure. Wait. WTF is an infrastructure-ish engineer? It's a software engineer who will be a full member of our engineering team, doing a mix of software development and operations. While this position is similar to what is often called a site reliability engineer or a devops engineer, we have no organizational silos. We expect and encourage all members of the engineering team to contribute wherever their skills and interests take them. For this particular position, however, we're looking for somebody whose skills and interests center around keeping our servers going 7 x 24. We're looking for somebody who can not just manage existing systems, but also drive improvements in infrastructure and process. You need to have the skills to develop tools to handle new situations where existing tools are inadequate. Our production envinronment is AWS-based, using Ubuntu Linux. Your responsibilities will include managing, deploying, and monitoring all of our AWS assets. Typical projects will include: Improving our server management and deployment processes. The goal is being able to roll out a new server instance, correctly configured for its role, with a single command. Improving system monitoring. We need to know quickly when any piece of hardware of software has failed or is operating out of normal limits. This includes our own servers as well as external providers. Improving our software deployment process, so new versions can be deployed faster. Improving processes for data backup, operational redundancy, and disaster recovery. Desired areas of experience: Managing cloud-based Linux servers in a 7 x 24 production environment Managing AWS assets, including EC2, S3, EMR Python for system management System management tools such as puppet, chef, fabic, boto Monitoring tools, including nagios, graphite, statsd, cloudwatch Managing large MongoDB installations Log management tools such as rsyslog and elasticsearch To apply, send resume (Word, PDF, or URL) to tech-jobs@songza.com. Account Manager Songza’s Account Manager is a critical part of the Sales Team. He or she will work with the Sales Team to ensure seamless campaign execution while providing high-level client service support. The success of all digital advertising campaigns lies in the hands of the Account Manager. The ideal candidate will be a key contributor within the Sales team and Songza as a whole. Responsibilities: Create dynamic, creative proposals and media plans that meet advertisers’ objectives and showcase what Songza has to offer Ensure online advertising campaigns are implemented in an accurate and timely manner Monitor campaigns and ensure campaign delivery across various ad serving platforms Analyze and optimize advertising performance to meet client KPIs and maximize profit Provide advertisers and/or agencies with campaign reporting when necessary Develop and nurture quality business relationships with clients Qualifications: Bachelor’s degree 2+ years of experience in client-facing, media account management roles Existing knowledge of DFP, MoPub and LiveRail are preferred Excellent organizational, analytical and time management skills Professional and polished written and verbal communication skills Ability to multi-task and deliver results under pressure Strong competence with Mac operating system and Microsoft Office suite of applications Strong work ethic; desire to work in an entrepreneurial environment Active on social media Team player Loves Songza! Sounds like you? Email: gab@songza.com with the Subject: \"Account Manager\". Yield Optimization Manager Songza’s mission is to make the things our users do every day better. Our Yield Optimization Manager will contribute to the success of our indirect sales channel by managing demand partner relationships across mobile, desktop, and video platforms; driving revenue from daily optimizations; and on-boarding new demand partners and monetization products. Songza’s Yield Optimization Manager will: Monitor existing demand partner relationships across mobile, desktop, and video platforms for performance and efficiency Optimize demand stack on a daily basis Evaluate potential new partners and coordinate with ad ops and development teams to prioritize on-boarding projects Use marketplace insight from demand partners to identify opportunities for audience development, new products, and revenue growth Oversee inventory management, forecasting, and yield management across all programmatic platforms Five Things About You. You have up to four years of prior experience with video and/or display ad serving platforms (DFP, MoPub, or Liverail preferred), third party demand UI’s (Rubicon, OpenX, iAd, AdExchange, etc) or yield optimization products. You are familiar with testing and implementing ad tags for programmatic deals. You have strong analytical skills and the ability to analyze performance data to drive inventory recommendations and troubleshoot issues. You have a keen attention to detail and experience handling multiple ongoing projects. You are passionate about being part of a fast-growing, disruptive start-up that improves the lives of millions of people every month. To apply, send salary requirements and resume to gina@songza.com, with the subject, \"Yield Optimization Manager\" Regional Sales Managers (New York, Chicago, Toronto) Songza’s mission is to make the things our users do every day better. We believe advertising on Songza should accomplish the same thing. Our native advertising solutions integrate brands into users’ daily routines by answering the most important customer question: \"How can this brand improve my day?\" Songza is looking for a regional sales manager to help us refine and scale the next generation of intent-based marketing with a solution that is native to the Songza user experience. This seller will be part of our founding sales team and will be critical in growing our revenue through \"Industry First\" initiatives as well as digital, audio, video and other pre-roll executions. We are looking for an individual who is entrepreneurial in spirit and thrives on building a book of business from the ground up. Songza’s Regional Sales Manager will: Proactively prospect, qualify, grow, and maintain a regional territory account list and manage activity with our CRM tool. Prospect and develop key ad agency and company relationships at all levels in order to effectively build and maintain territory ad revenue. Create exciting sales presentations, incorporating industry research and campaign performance data, and great mock-ups. Execute and deliver high quality responses to all RFPs based on client objectives and goals. Negotiate pricing and contractual agreements. Drive tons of new business! Seven things about you National media sales experience in either digital, mobile, radio, print, or video is required. A proven book of business is a plus. A minimum of 6 years of advertising sales experience with proven track record of exceeding sales goals and the ability to develop and manage a consistent sales pipeline. Contacts and relationships with leading agencies and clients in your territory. The ability to work across multiple agency departments (digital, broadcast, strategy, planning, and buying) to uncover different budgets and decision makers/ influencers. Excellent communication and presentation skills with extensive knowledge of digital and mobile media advertising and the overall ecosystem. A creative and fun spirit who inspires others, especially brand champions. Ability to meet and exceed quarterly revenue goals. Interested? Contact Us: Pete Roper | proper@songza.com. iOS Engineer As an iOS engineer, you will be responsible for all phases of development and testing, and deployment of our iOS products. You will work closely with our backend team to interface with the Songza HTTP API, and our graphic design experts to build a beautiful and fun to use user experience. You love shipping code. You love music. You have worked on large scale software projects. Like all our engineers, you are language-agnostic, but you're also an Objective-C wizard. You believe in automated testing and code review. You need to be able to work in a fast-paced, cloud-based development environment. We ship frequent updates to our mobile products to implement new features, fix bugs, and keep the user experience fresh. We're not slaves to any particular methodology, but neither do we believe in cowboy coding. Our goal is to find just enough structure to keep things from turning into chaos without getting bogged down in meaningless process. We don't have any hard and fast checklist of requirements, but these are the sorts of things we're looking for: 2+ years Objective-C and iOS programming experience Experience building universal apps and implementing custom views Automated testing of applications A solid understanding of HTTP and RESTful webservices Experience with some form of version control (we use mercurial) A bachelors in computer science or equivalent experience Most important, you must love working in a high-speed environment, where everybody makes a difference. Code we write in the morning is often in production the same afternoon. Your ability to drive technical decisions is a function of how good your design and code are, not your job title or how well you dress. To apply, send resume (Word, PDF or URL) and cover letter to tech-jobs@songza.com. Android Development Lead Songza is looking for somebody who can take over all phases of development, testing, and deployment of our existing Android products, and drive all new development efforts. You will be responsible for recruiting and mentoring an additional Android engineer to fill out our mobile development team. You will work closely with our backend team to interface with the Songza HTTP API, and our graphic design experts to build a beautiful and fun to use user experience. You love shipping code. You love music. You have worked on large scale software projects. Like all our engineers, you are language-agnostic, but you're also a Java wizard. You believe in automated testing and code review. You need to be able to work in a fast-paced, cloud-based development environment. We ship frequent updates to our mobile products to implement new features, fix bugs, and keep the user experience fresh. We're not slaves to any particular methodology, but neither do we believe in cowboy coding. Our goal is to find just enough structure to keep things from turning into chaos without getting bogged down in meaningless process. We don't have any hard and fast checklist of requirements, but these are the sorts of things we're looking for: Thorough knowledge of using Eclipse IDE and Android SDK Experience leading a development team Experience building Android apps from scratch utilizing standard SDK techniques Experience creating custom UI elements Experience delivering streaming media on Android Have shipped a commercialy viable Android app A bachelors in computer science or other relevant experience 2+ years of Android development experience Experience with HTTP, JSON, and REST Web Services Most important, you must love working in a high-speed environment, on a small team where everybody makes a difference. Your ability to drive technical decisions is a function of how good your design and code are, not your job title or how well you dress. To apply, send resume (Word, PDF or URL) and cover letter to tech-jobs@songza.com. Don't See What You're Looking For? Just because we don't list your dream job, that doesn't mean we don't want to hear from you. We've got a number of positions (engineering and otherwise) in the pipeline that we're not actively recruiting for right now. If the perfect person came along, we'd jump at the chance to bring them on board earlier than planned. Just send us a resume and a cover letter explaining why your life (and our employee list) won't be complete until you're part of the Songza team. For engineering jobs, send to tech-jobs@songza.com. For all other postions, jobs@songza.com. If you send to the wrong address, we can usually figure out what you meant and get it to the right person, but we'll make fun of you. So don't do that. See Us On Campus Songza participates in several academic career fairs over the year. Our on-campus recruiting schedule has wrapped up for spring 2013, but we'll be back on college campuses in the Fall. We'll be posting specific schools as we finalize our plans this summer, but if you're interested in getting your career off to a great start with Songza, there's no need to wait for us to visit your campus. Just drop an email to tech-jobs@songza.com (for engineering postions) or jobs@songza.com (for other postions). We'd love to talk with you. Songza plays you the right music at the right time. Made by Music Experts. 100% Free. No Audio Ads. Get the free Songza app © Songza Media, Inc. Advertising Careers Copyright Privacy Policy Terms of Service Twitter Facebook Google+", is_draft: true, company_id: 775, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, key_skill_one: "Android SDK", key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Mobile", description: "Songza is looking for somebody who can take over all phases of development, testing, and deployment of our existing Android products, and drive all new development efforts. You will be responsible for recruiting and mentoring an additional Android engineer to fill out our mobile development team."},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/consulting-engineer", title: "Consulting Engineer", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions Consulting Engineer New York, NY / Washington, DC / Palo Alto, CA MongoDB is looking for a team of consulting engineers to further our ongoing plans for world domination! As a technical consultant, you'll be MongoDB's ambassador to our clients and other MongoDB users. These positions are located in New York, Palo Alto, or Washington DC and will require North American travel (expected 50% of the time).Responsibilities You'll deliver advisory consulting to and lead comprehensive training sessions with MongoDB's clients, helping them solve mission-critical challenges in areas as varied as schema design, performance optimization (both in a database and in an application), software architecture, production operations When in the MongoDB office, you'll work with our team of software engineers and support staff to provide top-quality support for MongoDB users Requirements Excellent analytic and diagnostic skills are paramount, every other detail is negotiable 3+ years of software development/consulting/support experience desired Competence in at least one of the following languages (in no particular order): Java, C#, Ruby, PHP, Perl, Python, C++ Experience developing or supporting applications in a few different verticals is a plus Strong database knowledge is a plus; MongoDB experience is a double-plus You have a broad familiarity with enterprise-scale software architectures, application development methodologies, and deployment/operational considerations You're interested in a very customer-facing role, work well both alone and in teams (so excellent interpersonal and written communication skills are required) Apply now in New York, NY Apply now in Washington, DC Apply now in Palo Alto, CA About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading NoSQL database. Designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable. MongoDB enables new types of applications, better customer experience, faster time to market and lower costs. MongoDB has a thriving global community with more than 6 million downloads, 125,000 Online Education registrations, 25,000 MongoDB User Group (MUG) members and 20,000 annual MongoDB Days attendees. The company has more than 900 customers, including many of the world’s largest organizations. To all recruitment agencies: MongoDB does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias or MongoDB employees. MongoDB is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Life @ MongoDB 1 2 Did You Know? You can apply for a job using your LinkedIn account! Save time and include added resources by using LinkedIn to include your resume, work experience, and recommendations in your application. Apply Now With LinkedIn Apply now in New York, NYApply now in Washington, DCApply now in Palo Alto, CA Copyright © 2014 MongoDB, Inc. Legal Notices Information you submit as part of your application is subject to the MongoDB Jobs Privacy Policy", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, key_skill_one: nil, key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Consulting", description: nil},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/associate-technical-services-engineer", title: "Associate Technical Services Engineer", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions Associate Technical Services Engineer New York, NY Servicing the most popular NoSQL database, with growth in every industry vertical, presents new challenges every day. Successful members of the Technical Services team will not only be comfortable diving into these uncharted waters but will be excited to solve the problems our diverse customers face. Team members will apply strong problem solving skills and will acquire a broad understanding of our products as well as a wide range of innovative customer applications and environments, from Foursquare to CERN to Metlife and everywhere in-between. At the end of the day, you’ll be able to look at these groundbreaking applications and say that you had a hand in making them happen. The Technical Services team at MongoDB, Inc. is responsible for ensuring customer success in their use of MongoDB through: consulting on application or schema design optimizing performance and solving scalability issues resolving production outages designing and reviewing operational procedures like business continuity plans explaining the internals of MongoDB Responsibilities Help our customers succeed by solving their challenging technical problems, all the way from design through to production operations. This means working on hands-on customer issues, and escalating problems as needed Helping to mentor less experienced members of the team, and to recruit new members of the team. This includes assisting with phone screens and in-person interviews Contribute to internal technical projects, which can include software development, benchmarking, building documentation and training guides, and providing oversight on other engineers’ project work Optional, but encouraged: interact with the community at meetups and conferences Requirements 2-4 years in one or more of the following (ideally with some experience in the rest): Software development, Application design, Systems administration, Network administration, Database administration, Data architecture and design, Performance tuning and benchmarking, Technical Support on back-end services (example: databases) Excellent communication skills, written and verbal The ability to think on your feet, remain calm under pressure, and solve problems in real-time Strong diagnostic/ troubleshooting process, with significant experience troubleshooting real, end-to-end technical issues The desire and ability to rapidly learn a wide variety of new technical skills Nice to Haves Experience coding in one or more of Java, PHP, Python, Ruby, C, C++, C#, Javascript Experience administering large-scale production environments, including hardware, operating systems (Linux or Windows), networks (including firewalls and load balancers) Experience managing large scale databases (RDBMS or NoSQL or both) Experience using or managing MongoDB Language skills (Japanese, Mandarin, German, Spanish, French are all plusses) Basic team leadership or management skills, preferably with hands-on experience Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading NoSQL database. Designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable. MongoDB enables new types of applications, better customer experience, faster time to market and lower costs. MongoDB has a thriving global community with more than 6 million downloads, 125,000 Online Education registrations, 25,000 MongoDB User Group (MUG) members and 20,000 annual MongoDB Days attendees. The company has more than 900 customers, including many of the world’s largest organizations. To all recruitment agencies: MongoDB does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias or MongoDB employees. MongoDB is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Life @ MongoDB 1 2 Did You Know? You can apply for a job using your LinkedIn account! Save time and include added resources by using LinkedIn to include your resume, work experience, and recommendations in your application. Apply Now With LinkedIn Apply now in New York, NY Copyright © 2014 MongoDB, Inc. Legal Notices Information you submit as part of your application is subject to the MongoDB Jobs Privacy Policy", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, key_skill_one: nil, key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Technical Services", description: nil},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/network-engineer", title: "Network Engineer", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions Network Engineer New York, NY You are a Network Engineer with experience designing and implementing multiple networks globally. Your job will be to create and maintain a secure network between our offices, EC2, and co-located data centers. In this critical role, you will be the network specialist within our fast-paced DevOps Team. Responsibilities Configure and maintain the network infrastructure for our office, data centers, and production environment Build a secure, globally distributed environment for MongoDB Work within our DevOps Team to create scalable networks, and improve our existing network Requirements 5+ years of experience working with Cisco and Juniper products Experience building and maintaining a globally distributed network You have worked with multiple networking protocols, including BGP Basic knowledge of Linux systems Experience with Meraki networks is a plus Familiarity with scripting languages (Python, JavaScript, Perl) and with MongoDB a big plus Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading NoSQL database. Designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable. MongoDB enables new types of applications, better customer experience, faster time to market and lower costs. MongoDB has a thriving global community with more than 6 million downloads, 125,000 Online Education registrations, 25,000 MongoDB User Group (MUG) members and 20,000 annual MongoDB Days attendees. The company has more than 900 customers, including many of the world’s largest organizations. To all recruitment agencies: MongoDB does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias or MongoDB employees. MongoDB