  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/java-application-engineer", title: "Java Application Engineer", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions Java Application Engineer New York, NY MongoDB is looking for a server-side Java engineer to join us in building the best database monitoring system on the planet. We have recently launched MMS, a freely available, cloud-based monitoring and alerting system for MongoDB. MMS is already being used to monitor thousands of MongoDB nodes and processes billions of metrics per day. There is tons to do to make it even better and to scale the system as we rapidly add new customers.Responsibilities Design, implement, and test core MMS features in a small team environment Assist ops team to troubleshoot operational issues with MMS itself Assist support team in using MMS to troubleshoot customer issues with MongoDB Requirements Expert Java engineer with 2+ years experience building web applications, front to back Experience with multi-threaded applications and concurrency Some experience of scripting (e.g. Python) a plus Familiarity with JSP/JavaScript a plus Familiarity with MongoDB a big plus Nice to haves You want to be part of a great team working at the forefront of database technology innovation You're flexible. You'll be joining a small team, so you're willing to take on a wide variety of responsibilities You are well organized, used to keeping many balls in the air at the same time You realize that comprehensive testing is your responsibility as a developer Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading NoSQL database. Designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable. MongoDB enables new types of applications, better customer experience, faster time to market and lower costs. MongoDB has a thriving global community 