  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/online-education-summer-software-engineering-intern", title: "Online Education, Summer Software Engineering", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions Online Education, Summer Software Engineering Intern New York, NY You will work with engineers on the education team to build an interactive lesson track that teaches students how to use MongoDB using the technology framework at codecademy.com. Today, codecademy has no direct support for MongoDB lessons, although they use MongoDB to deploy their platform. Your first task will be to build the software that allows online assessment of MongoDB skills in the browser, possibly leveraging the existing MongoDB-in-a-browser work. You will build an extension to codecademy that will allow anyone to create interactive MongoDB lesson tracks, and then you will implement the first track so that the millions of users of codecademy can learn about MongoDB. This will be a 10 week internship with the possibility of an extension. Requirements In the process of receiving a BS or MS in Computer Science Interested in online education Experience with front-end web development Experience with mobile development a plus Prior experience with MongoDB and a genuine interest in databases a HUGE plus! Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading NoSQL database. Designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable. MongoDB enables new types of applications, better customer experience, faster time to market and lower costs. MongoDB has a thriving global community with more than 6 million downloads, 125,000 Online Education registrations, 25,000 MongoDB User Group (MUG) members and 20,000 annual MongoDB Days attendees. The company has more than 900 customers, including many of the world’s largest organizations. To all recruitment agencies: MongoDB does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias or MongoDB employees. MongoDB is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Life @ MongoDB 1 2 Did You Know? You can apply for a job using your LinkedIn account! Save time and include added resources by using LinkedIn to include your resume, work experience, and recommendations in your application. Apply Now With LinkedIn Apply now in New York, NY Copyright © 2014 MongoDB, Inc. Legal Notices Information you submit as part of your application is subject to the MongoDB Jobs Privacy Policy", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, key_skill_one: "BS", key_skill_two: "MS", sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil},
  {link: "http://www.adaptly.com/job_listings/26", title: "Director of Software Engineering", full_text: "Request A DemoLog In Contact Us Home Solutions Technology Work with Us Case Studies About Us Team Timeline Investors Press Careers Blog Back to Careers Director of Software Engineering We are looking for Director of Software Engineering to lead our Software Engineering team based in NYC. As a hands-on leader, you’re comfortable getting your hands dirty and writing your share of code as well as managing the team. Additionally, you’ll help establish standards and best practices for development of all of our products and technologies. You’re a believer in Agile methodologies, contribute to the open source community, and are constantly learning and working to improve your craft. ROLES & RESPONSIBILITIES Day-to-day leadership, mentoring and growth of our core team of software engineers. Work in partnership with our Product, Test and TechOps teams to ensure that our products and services are world class. Identify and implement appropriate design, development and testing methodologies, best practices, coding standards, documentation and tools. In conjunction with the CTO, own and manage software development roadmaps in alignment with product, engineering and business priorities. Act as a senior architect for the team; assist in coding, testing, debugging, and documenting of applications. REQUIREMENTS Demonstrated experience leading the development of consumer grade, high-volume/high-availability software applications. Expert in software design methodologies and experience with multiple programming languages such as Ruby, Java, Clojure, Python, Go, etc. Strong experience with agile software development values and practices, such as Scrum. Prior experience with test-driven development and continuous integration. Strong SQL and RDBMS data modeling skills, as well as experience with various NoSQL technologies such as document databases or key value stores. Experience with Ruby/Rails, PostgresSQL, Hadoop/Hive, Redshift, Cassandra, Redis, Storm preferred. Experience with cloud hosting providers such as AWS and/or Heroku. 5+ years management experience in a software engineering organization of 10+ engineers 10+ years of software development experience. MS or BS in Computer Science or related field. Employee Spotlight SEAN SHILLO VP of Engineering \"At Adaptly, trying to disrupt social advertising and redefine established concepts is what we breathe. I wake up every day excited to tackle difficult challenges with brilliant people and have fun doing it.\" To apply Submit your resume here to apply. Technology Work with Us Case Studies Team Timeline Investors Press Careers Blog Twitter PMD Facebook PMD Center Adaptly NYC 22 W. 19th St. Third Floor New York, NY 10011 Adaptly Los Angeles 736 Lincoln Blvd. Suite #2 Venice, CA 90291 Adaptly Chicago 222 W. Merchandise Mart Plaza #1212 Chicago, IL 60654 Adaptly International 2nd Floor 68/69 St Martins Lane London, WC2N 4JS Connect with us! facebook linkedin twitter github Made in New York © Adaptly Inc. All Rights Reserved. Adaptly is a registered trademark. All other marks are property of their respective owners. Privacy × Request a Demo × Thank you! Someone from our sales team will be in touch with you shortly.", is_draft: true, company_id: 25, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 5, key_skill_one: nil, key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Executive", description: nil},
  {link: "http://www.axial.net/about/careers/", title: "Python Engineer", full_text: "Axial Network Search Events Leaderboards Pricing Case Studies Case Studies Testimonials Transactions Resources M&A Blog Entrepreneur Blog Library About Team Careers Sign In Careers Axial is building a platform that will transform how private companies connect with capital. The Axial network is an online marketplace connecting people, information and capital. Our vision is to enable every private company to successfully finance or sell their company. Our team is small still and we are recruiting exceptional people into every role. No matter what the position, we look for three things: You have a history of doing things exceptionally well, academically, athletically or professionally You are focused, driven, intelligent, and have a bias for action You are happy, friendly and a natural communicator; you add energy to the room Account Management Account ManagerAs an Account Manager at Axial, you’ll be fanatical about solving for and delivering what Axial Members need to succeed. You’ll lead the post-sale efforts in building relationships with your Members. You’ll become a domain expert in business development across the entrepreneurial economy for people who invest in, acquire, or advise private companies in this day and age.Read MoreAccount Manager Why Member Success? As an Account Manager at Axial, you’ll be fanatical about solving for and delivering what Axial Members need to succeed. You’ll lead the post-sale efforts in building relationships with your Members. You’ll become a domain expert in business development across the entrepreneurial economy for people who invest in, acquire, or advise private companies in this day and age. You will become an expert on the Axial product so you can intelligently teach and advise Members on the best ways to engage with the Axial network. At Axial, we are extremely passionate about the success of our Members for two main reasons: 1. We’re committed to excellence. Axial delivers the most critical online business development tools to the buyers, investors, advisors and CEOs in the private markets. We’re committed to delivering the best possible consulting and thought leadership to our Members. 2. We believe in our mission. Creating long-term relationships with our Members is absolutely crucial to our success. We must delight them in order to sustain them and grow. How will you do it? You will become a business development consultant to every Member you serve You will become an expert on private equity, entrepreneurship, and investment banking You will onboard and educate new Members on their Axial Membership You will teach Members best practices and provide expert insight You will build long-term relationships with Members to ensure they remain with Axial You will save at-risk Members through intense value-driving negotiations You will serve as a liaison between customers and our Product & Engineering teams You will be the face of Axial at our regular in-person meetings and events with Members You will contribute to the strategic direction of the company, as well as to the evolution of the product You will be measured by your abilities to a) influence your Members to engage with Axial and b) retain long-term Memberships with existing Members What We’re Seeking Highly passionate and engaging individuals with the ability to connect authentically with others Intellectually curious thinkers with a need to constantly uncover information and solve problems Exceptionally impressive communicators, written and verbal True hospitable nature and a passion for making people happy, challenged, and delighted Energy and capacity to handle constant change and make quick decisions Tenacity and grit. You hate to lose, you love to win, and your work ethic is through the roof. Ability to speak up, rattle the cage, question the status quo to push the team forward Highly collaborative people who win when their team wins Bachelors Degree or higher One to three years work experience, preferably in a customer-facing role Apply Administrative Executive Assistant to CEOWe are seeking a seasoned, trusted, and competent Executive/Personal Assistant to serve the professional and personal needs of our CEO. We are a fast-growth technology company headquartered in the Flatiron. Our environment is casual, friendly, and transparent, but we demand excellence and maintain extremely high standards. Read MoreExecutive Assistant to CEO We are seeking a seasoned, trusted, and competent Executive/Personal Assistant to serve the professional and personal needs of our CEO. We are a fast-growth technology company headquartered in the Flatiron. Our environment is casual, friendly, and transparent, but we demand excellence and maintain extremely high standards. The CEO needs the following: Someone who can help him manage all facets of his life; the role will be roughly 70% EA and 30% PA Someone who wants to work in a fast growing company environment while also handling personal and family items, errands, and commitments around town and at his home Someone who has extraordinary detail orientation You must be able to take on a heavy professional and personal calendar, billing, travel and vacation logistics, financial wires for investments, and managing personal vendors You must develop a direct relationship and rapport with his family to be successful Someone who is always responsive, has a sense of urgency, gets it done right reliably Extremely discreet. You will be entrusted with considerable amounts of private information. No slip-ups, no poor judgment Energetic, cheerful, consistently positive attitude Ideally, this person would work for the CEO for the very long-term Requirements: You are a career executive assistant; this is your profession, you excel in it, you love the role of being the trusted gatekeeper, coordinator and partner to the CEO 10+ years as an EA / PA working in demanding fast-paced and rapidly changing environments Experience with complex calendar management Experience interacting discreetly, professionally and wisely with executives, vendors, family members, etc Experience with putting together small dinners / events, etc Experience getting around Manhattan Must be responsive; you’re not on call 24/7, but you’ve got to be available and responsive Apply Engineering Python EngineerAs a Python Engineer at Axial, you will build data-service backends using the Flask and Django web-application frameworks. You will work on the same team as Product Managers, Designers and Front-End Engineers who specify, design and build products and widgets that consume your data-services.Read MorePython Engineer As a Python Engineer at Axial, you will build data-service backends using the Flask and Django web-application frameworks. You will work on the same team as Product Managers, Designers and Front-End Engineers who specify, design and build products and widgets that consume your data-services. Axial’s mission is to enable every private company to access the capital needed to finance or exit their business. Your software will connect entrepreneurs, investors, brokers and business advisors, driving the largest network of private investors in the world. The Problems You’ll SolveAs an engineer at Axial, you will solve difficult technical problems so our Members don’t have to. Some of our biggest technical challenges right now are: Search. Search connects entrepreneurs, and their advisors with capital and services. By constantly improving search, we help our Members: – secure the capital needed to finance or sell their business – connect and build relationships – constantly improve relevancy Shared Authorization Framework. We serve both small businesses and large companies. If you’ve ever wanted to build a licensing management system that manages user, group and feature access required to support the disparate needs of smallest and largest companies in the world, we’re your destination. Go SOA. We believe our data is our business, and we believe that decoupled data-services give us the maximum flexibility and utility in accessing our data. The Axial Corps of EngineersWe are a team of 8 engineers dedicated to achieving excellence in every aspect and level of our system, from our automated build system to our increasingly modular front-ends. In pursuit of excellence, we focus on one thing at a time, one area at a time, one day at a time. Our slogan is “Factum non Verbum”, “Actions not Words”: We ship improvements to our product every day Simplicity and flexibility are our guide We change our minds when we’re proven wrong You’re an ideal candidate if you … communicate and collaborate well are a seasoned python expert have designed and implemented distributed HTTP data services have extensive SQL experience have worked with git are experienced working with and managing a *NIX system love flat, repeatable data structures The benefits of being an Axialite … competitive salary competitive equity we buy you all the books you need conveniently located Flatiron office (near 4/5/6/N/R/Q/L/F) Apply Front-End EngineerAxial’s engineers develop technology to drive the transformation and democratization of modern capital markets. In addition to leveraging and building search technology to transform an entire industry, our engineers use their skills to advance our data, social and other technology-driven product strategies and initiatives.Read MoreFront-End Engineer The Area: Software Engineering Axial’s engineers develop technology to drive the transformation and democratization of modern capital markets. In addition to leveraging and building search technology to transform an entire industry, our engineers use their skills to advance our data, social and other technology-driven product strategies and initiatives. The Role As a Front-End Engineer at Axial, you’re responsible for developing and refining the client-facing HTML, Javascript and CSS portions of our platform. We’re a tight-knit team here so collaboration is a must. You’ll be building technology hands-on with a small product and design team, and be responsible for prototyping and creating responsive and elegant UIs to drive site engagement and manageability. You’ll also be working to help us improve our service aggregators, applications templating, and client-side libraries, and to extend and improve the power and scale of the Axial platform. You will be challenged to deconstruct designs into fine-grained, distributed modules capable of reuse in any portion of our platform. You’ll be challenged to engineer great, sustainable technology at high speed, but that’s okay ‘cause you’re a champ. We look for technologists who: - Are expert at working with JavaScript, HTML, and CSS- Are intimately familiar with browser quirks- Love creating well-crafted interfaces and elegant web UI’s- Communicate and collaborate well Bonus points for: - Bootstrap, jQuery, or Django- Experience developing in *NIX environments- Experience with a non-JavaScript programming language (python, php, ruby, perl, sh) The benefits of being an Axialite … we are building something very important the team you’re joining is pretty darn good and getting better with every new hire we pay people what they’re worth, not what we can get away with stocked and ever-expanding technical library onsite stocked fridge and bottomless coffee bike-friendly good location w/ roof in the Flatiron Apply Marketing Marketing ManagerAxial is looking for a driven inbound marketer interested in helping build a rapidly growing business. You’d be a great fit at Axial if you act like an entrepreneur (scrappy, smart, efficient, self-directed) and want to contribute to the success of an organization serving the Entrepreneurial Economy. You know that marketing is critical to growing a business and care deeply about inbound marketing.Read MoreMarketing Manager Axial is looking for a driven inbound marketer interested in helping build a rapidly growing business. You’d be a great fit at Axial if you act like an entrepreneur (scrappy, smart, efficient, self-directed) and want to contribute to the success of an organization serving the Entrepreneurial Economy. You know that marketing is critical to growing a business and care deeply about inbound marketing. You love Panda and Penguin because they just made the kind of marketing that you love to do that much stronger. You know the behavioral differences between LinkedIn Ads and Adwords. And you care deeply about what data can tell us about our marketing (and what it can’t). You know more than anything that you want to work for a great company where you can take ownership of projects and see them all the way through to completion. You want a place where you do everything in marketing – from creating all your own campaigns (meaty reports, lighthearted snackable content, and everything in between), sending emails, setting up specific landing pages, reaching out to the press and people on Twitter and on and on. About Marketing at Axial We have a belief that good marketers don’t just understand one part of the job. We’re all full stack inbound marketers running our own campaigns from start to finish, accountable for production, distribution, measurement and results. We work with designers or drop into InDesign ourselves to finish up big content pieces, build out landing pages in WordPress, set up ad campaigns, manage lead nurturing processes in Eloqua and run analytics on our own campaigns. Owning the whole process makes us much better at what we do – and helps us all build the skills we need to be successful versatile marketers over the long run. What You’ll Do: – Writing, writing, writing: blog articles, in-depth reports, and downloadable content and offers – Constantly experiment with new content types, topics, formats, and ideas – Build and optimize landing pages – Develop high-performing ad campaigns – Write emails and build nurturing campaigns – Interview successful entrepreneurs and investors in entrepreneurs – Analyze and report on your campaign performance How Success within Marketing and within Axial is Measured – The extent to which you elevate the quality of your teammates – Your contribution to a work environment organized around sustainable high performance – Inbound leads generated – Organic traffic finding your content & campaigns – Number of downloads of your content & campaigns – Organic blog subscriber growth and social media follower growth Musts: – 5+ years of relevant marketing experience – A love for writing and publishing and a card-carrying believer in inbound marketing – Exceptional written communications, with previous writing experience, blogging or journalism – A consistent sense of urgency and curiosity in all of your work – A demonstrable desire to market to and serve the entrepreneurial economy – Ability to link all activities to key ROI metrics and other business objectives Does this sound like you? If so, please attach a resume and a writing sample or two. Apply Marketing EngineerAxial is looking for a software developer to support the work of the broader marketing team by building and maintaining the technical infrastructure to help grow a world class marketing organization. Over the past five years we have built the largest network for the entrepreneurial economy and we want to add a person to handle the development and ongoing maintenance of the Axial website, technical integration with our CRM platforms, and marketing analytics.Read MoreMarketing Engineer Axial is looking for a software developer to support the work of the broader marketing team by building and maintaining the technical infrastructure to help grow a world class marketing organization. Over the past five years we have built the largest network for the entrepreneurial economy and we want to add a person to handle the development and ongoing maintenance of the Axial website, technical integration with our CRM platforms, and marketing analytics. The Role: You are a top-notch developer with a keen interest in helping facilitate the growth of the largest network available for entrepreneurs to grow, finance or sell their business. You will utilize machine learning to dynamically personalize our website to maximize engagement and conversions. You will take sole ownership of building major customizations and add-ons to our public facing site, including integrations with third party API’s. You will drive direct business growth using your technical skills. The Problems You Will Solve: You will have the opportunity to wear lots of hats and contribute on a number of levels including: Developing internal marketing reporting and analytics tools using cutting edge programming languages such as Python Building tools and plug-ins that can contribute to the open source community Translating complex data sets into insightful and meaningful visualizations Managing API integrations between website, analytics software, and internal systems Creating rich interactive experiences for our Axial WordPress CMS through custom PHP and MySQL development Apply Product Development Product ManagerAt Axial, the Product Development Team leads the way in product innovation. We are the driving force responsible for conceptualizing, shaping, and launching new products. At the core of our work is an authentic commitment to doing whatever maximizes success for our user base. At Axial, we call our users “Members”. We strive to learn everything we can about them -- their needs, their behaviors, their lives. This informs every decision we make and every product we ship.Read MoreProduct Manager Product Development @ AxialAt Axial, the Product Development Team leads the way in product innovation. We are the driving force responsible for conceptualizing, shaping, and launching new products. At the core of our work is an authentic commitment to doing whatever maximizes success for our user base. At Axial, we call our users “Members”. We strive to learn everything we can about them — their needs, their behaviors, their lives. This informs every decision we make and every product we ship. The Product Manager Role Product Managers at Axial lead the ideation process, define the product, and work with Engineering to launch new products and features. Product Managers are part of a multi-disciplinary team of product development, design, QA, and UX professionals who collaborate closely with each other to build products that touch millions of people. Product Managers at Axial are data-driven, critical thinkers with a strong understanding of technical application development, the right design sense, and an exceptional ability to interpret user behavior and intent. Responsibilities:- Drive all stages of the product development life cycle.- Deeply understand the market opportunity and identify the needs of our “Members,” to create new and improve existing Axial products- Effectively strategize, organize, and communicate new ideas and concepts to the organization at large- Create requirements for new products and features, and work with rest of the Product Development and Engineering teams to manage the end-to-end implementation Qualifications:- BA/BS degree, preferably in Computer Science or related field- 4+ years of relevant work experience in an outstanding product organization- Experience building products with agile product development principles- Ability to lead productive brainstorming sessions and create thoughtful product plans- Great teammate, great attitude. Arrogance, snarkiness, or immaturity isn’t tolerated- Drive and urgency to build great products- You are an exceptional communicator in all contexts: written, spoken, internal, external Preferred Qualifications:- Direct experience launching notable products in early stage or high-growth environments- Understanding of web-based data and analytic models- Prototyping capabilities Apply Sales Account Executive - Private CompaniesThe Private Companies (PC) sales team at Axial is responsible for recruiting and introducing owners and operators of private companies to intermediary Members on the Axial network. PC Account Executives are highly effective communicators who are able to correspond with senior level executives across various industries and enterprise sizes.Read MoreAccount Executive – Private Companies What is a Private Companies (“PC”) Account Executive?The Private Companies (PC) sales team at Axial is responsible for recruiting and introducing owners and operators of private companies to intermediary Members on the Axial network. PC Account Executives are highly effective communicators who are able to correspond with senior level executives across various industries and enterprise sizes. PC Account Executives are resourceful sales professionals who employ a consultative approach to helping CEOs, business owners, and entrepreneurs achieve their long-term growth, financing, or exit objectives through the use of our tools and products. We are passionate about helping private companies achieve the best outcome possible for their businesses. The Role: As a PC Account Executive, your day will be composed of three primary activities. First is outbound prospecting to engage owners and operators of private companies. Second is onboarding these private companies and connecting them with investment bankers, M&A advisors, and other Members of the Axial Network. Third is ongoing education, training, and relationship management to ensure private companies continue to engage with Members. You will achieve success by generating high levels of new conversations, effectively training private companies to engage with Members, and demonstrating how these companies can reach their longer-term goals more successfully with the help of our Members. Our team is highly driven and values collaboration and transparency. Minimum Qualifications: Track record of over-achieving goals in prior positions History of setting goals and achieving them, in the classroom, playing field, or in business Prior participation in a winning team environment 0-2 years of trained sales experience OR financial services experience Exceptional verbal and written communication skills Bachelors Degree or higher Personal Qualifications: You are committed to your success and will do what it takes to achieve your goals You are comfortable with interfacing with senior-level executives Enjoy winning the trust of those around you and developing relationships Highly personable and able to connect with prospects on a human level You love to win, more than you hate to lose You have a committed work ethic to personal and team goals Learn more about the Axial Member Development team by reviewing our culture deck, titled The Axial Way. Click here Apply Sales AssociateThe Member Origination Associate (MOA) team at Axial is responsible for outbound prospecting and recruiting new prospective Members into conversations with Sales Executives. MOAs are are highly effective communicators and able to gain access to senior-level executives and distinguish between their unique business needs across a wide various of industries (private equity, venture capital, investment banking, commercial lending, business brokers, family offices, etc.).Read MoreSales Associate Our Sales Associates are Member Origination Associates (“MOA”): The Member Origination Associate (MOA) team at Axial is responsible for outbound prospecting and recruiting new prospective Members into conversations with Sales Executives. MOAs are are highly effective communicators and able to gain access to senior-level executives and distinguish between their unique business needs across a wide various of industries (private equity, venture capital, investment banking, commercial lending, business brokers, family offices, etc.). MOAs specialize in high quality communication over phone, voicemail, and email. They are creative and find ways to help