 of Sales Operations Do At Axial? The Associate of Sales Operations at Axial will be responsible for supporting the Sales Operations Manager and helping build the sales operations and strategy function at Axial. There are two core operations responsibilities relating to the Sales Operations function. The primary responsibility centers around Salesforce productivity and Salesforce enablement. This is a wide-ranging responsibility and includes everything from appropriate inbound lead assignment (developed in conjunction with the marketing organization) to assisting in territory development to the identification of necessary resources to accelerate talk time for the sales team. Finally, the last responsibility relates to the reduction of organizational churn through the development of dashboards, systems, and analytics to help the Member Success organization in account management and account support. The Sales Operations Team The Sales Operations team at Axial is led by the Manager of Sales Operations but will include the Associate of Sales Operations as a critical direct report, responsible for helping build and develop the function. The Sales Operations team will also include a set of temporary and offshore resources, primarily responsible for data management and data integrity. As the team grows the Sales Ops Associate will have an opportunity to oversee these functions. At first, the Sales Operations Associate will be asked to roll up their sleeves and dive into the work itself – becoming an expert on Salesforce reporting, analytics, workflows, uploads, and lead assignment sequences to enable the acceleration of the Sales Operations function at Axial. Specific Objectives 1. Maintain and manage the size of the Axial database sufficient to support near-term go-to-market strategy 2. Materially increase revenue and productivity per sales person 3. Decrease sales person ramp time to on-target productivity 4. Decrease churn and Accounts at Risk through the development of dashboards, analytics supporting the Member Success organization 5. Increase Operational Efficiency (Billing, Fulfillment, Collections) Responsibilities:● Build Salesforce workflows and protocols to allow for efficient lead and territory allocation ● Work with a team of offshore and onsite resources to grow the Axial database, clean qualified accounts, and oversee all data integrity ● Track, report and discover valuable new sales operations metrics to determine business health and trends ● Work cross-functionally to maintain and improve Salesforce dashboards for all teams ● Develop new workflows and protocols to drive sales productivity and sales team enablement ● Conduct ongoing data analysis of user base to enable “Members for Life”: Programs to identify Members at risk before renewal date Programs to identify win-win opportunities to increase Member Success & ACV Establish strong working relationships with finance, Member Development, Marketing, Member Success, & Engineering teams to achieve above objectives without constant management involvement Requirements: ● 0-2 years experience, previous roles as a consultant, business analyst, or finance analyst OR voracious appetite to learn and develop those skills ● Ability to master Salesforce.com: objects, data quality, custom workflows, reporting, and dashboard tools ● Exceptional problem solving and analytical skills, including experience with complex data structures and models ● Aptitude for Excel, for all forms of analysis and data modelling ● SQL knowledge (or other querying languages) and experience with data warehousing technologies a plus ● Ability to demonstrate thought leadership, present rigorous analysis and insights with clarity and confidence ● Can-do attitude willing to lead by example, do whatever it takes to succeed, and shift altitudes between high-level strategic planning and low-level tactical database administration and support Apply Sales Operations ManagerThe Manager of Sales Operations at Axial will be responsible for the senior leadership of the Sales Operations function. The overall goal of the Manager of Sales Operations is to work closely with the Head of Sales & Member Development to build and develop a first-class sales organization and to contribute both strategic and tactical insights to enable that development. Read MoreSales Operations Manager What Will The Manager of Sales Operations Do At Axial?The Manager of Sales Operations at Axial will be responsible for the senior leadership of the Sales Operations function. The overall goal of the Manager of Sales Operations is to work closely with the Head of Sales & Member Development to build and develop a first-class sales organization and to contribute both strategic and tactical insights to enable that development. There are three core strategic responsibilities relating to the Sales Operations function. The first is go-to-market strategy. This includes developing an overall go-to-market plan for new customer segments, helping map and size the market for potential new Axial Members, and growing the size of the near-term addressable market through database management and oversight. The second primary responsibility centers around Salesforce productivity and Salesforce enablement. This is a wide-ranging responsibility and includes everything from appropriate inbound lead assignment (developed in conjunction with the marketing organization) to territory development to quota and compensation plan development to the identification of necessary resources to accelerate talk time for the sales team. Finally, the last responsibility relates to the reduction of organizational churn through the development of dashboards, systems, and analytics to help the Member Success organization in account management and account support. The Sales Operations Team The Sales Operations team at Axial will be led by the Manager of Sales Operations but will also include additional teammates and direct reports as well as a set of ancillary support resources. The Manager of Sales Operations will oversee one immediate direct report, a Sales Operations Associate, as well as a group of paid interns and offshore resources focused on database management and data integrity. The Manager of Sales Ops will also manage a dedicated Salesforce Developer who will be responsible for custom development of our Salesforce instance to further support our sales and Member Development team. Specific Objectives Maintain and manage the size of the Axial database sufficient to support near-term go-to-market strategy Materially increase revenue and productivity per sales person Decrease sales person ramp time to on-target productivity Decrease churn and Accounts at Risk through the development of dashboards, analytics supporting the Member Success organization Increase Operational Efficiency (Billing, Fulfillment, Collections) Help management improve decision-making regarding pricing and go-to-market issues Responsibilities Manage a team of offshore and onsite resources to grow the Axial database, clean qualified accounts, and oversee all data integrity Oversee Salesforce workflows and protocols to allow for efficient lead and territory allocation Develop new workflows and protocols to drive sales productivity and sales team enablement Track, report and discover valuable new sales operations metrics to determine business health and trends Conduct ongoing data analysis of user base to enable “Members for Life”: Programs to identify Members at risk before renewal date Programs to identify win-win opportunities to increase Member Success & ACV Work cross-functionally to maintain and improve Salesforce dashboards for all teams Go-to-market territory analysis and coverage, re-alignment Analyze and contribute to sales compensation models / designs Deliver executive level updates in key leadership meetings (Quarterly Business Reviews, etc.) Gain management confidence such that the insights you produce are utilized in executive and board level presentations Establish strong working relationships with finance, Member Development, Marketing, Member Success, & Engineering teams to achieve above objectives without constant management involvement Requirements: 5-7+ years industry experience with previous experience as a consultant, business analyst, or finance analyst Mastery of Salesforce.com: objects, data quality, custom workflows, reporting, and dashboard tools Exceptional problem solving and analytical skills, including experience with complex data structures and models Expert in Excel, for all forms of analysis and data modelling SQL knowledge (or other querying languages) and experience with data warehousing technologies a plus Ability to demonstrate thought leadership, present rigorous analysis and insights with clarity and confidence Ability and/or interest and aptitude in growing and leading teams Can-do attitude willing to lead by example, do whatever it takes to succeed, and shift altitudes between high-level strategic planning and low-level tactical database administration and support Apply Sales Executive - PCM TeamThe Private Capital Markets (PCM) sales team at Axial is responsible for identifying and recruiting new capital providers onto the Axial Network. Sales Executives are highly effective communicators and able to correspond with senior level executives at various types of investment firms (private equity, family offices, debt funds, VC funds, independent sponsors, senior lenders, commercial banks, etc.).Read MoreSales Executive – PCM Team What is a Private Capital Markets (“PCM”) Sales Executive? The Private Capital Markets sales team at Axial is responsible for identifying and recruiting new capital providers onto the Axial Network. Sales Executives are highly effective communicators and able to correspond with senior level executives at various types of investment firms (private equity, family offices, debt funds, VC funds, independent sponsors, senior lenders, 