  {link: "http://www.asheavenue.com/careers/", title: "FRONT-END DEVELOPER", full_text: "Ashe Avenue Contact Blog Careers Services Team Work Careers Back-End Developer Ashe Avenue is searching for an adventurous spirit to join our development team. Do you enjoy experimenting with new technologies? Do you enjoy contributing to the open-source world? Do you find optimization, caching, server architecture, and object-oriented or MVC programming enjoyable? While we typically shun labels, we are looking for a back-end team member with a passion for server-side development. You must possess a feverish desire to produce top quality, D.R.Y. code. You must be comfortable working in a fast-paced environment and wired to research and look for the newest tools, technologies or libraries. You must enjoy jumping between languages, environments and projects while never letting your skills stagnate. You will be working with skilled developers across our Brooklyn and Chapel Hill offices, and collaborate with members of the front-end team to produce high-profile, client-facing work. We have offices in Brooklyn, NY and Chapel Hill, NC so the candidate should live in either of those areas. Please send your resume to jobs [at] asheavenue.com, and be sure to include your GitHub page or links to work you’ve done. Requirements: At least 2 years developing professionally in Ruby, PHP, or server-side Javascript, plus a desire to continually add to your language portfolio Strong understanding and experience with web application frameworks like Rails, Yii, Cake, or Express, etc. Comfort with modern databases, either Postgres, MySQL, or any of the various NoSQL databases (Mongo, Rethink, Couch, etc.) A preference for developing in an agency, consulting, or startup environment Natural curiosity, hunger, and a desire to progress through fast-paced client work Experience with native mobile application development for iOS or Android is preferred but not required. Comfortable working in Linux environments Experience working with Git Nice-to-haves: DevOps or sysadmin experience Experience with native mobile application development for iOS or Android Open-source contributions We offer full health benefits, 401k plans, and employee incentive programs. We love technology, music, and art. We could be your new home. Drop us a line. Seriously. jobs [at] asheavenue.com. Front-End Developer Ashe Avenue is looking for an experienced Front-end Developer responsible for producing HTML markup, CSS and client-side engineering solutions for websites and web applications. The position requires extensive knowledge and understanding of HTML, CSS and JavaScript. This role is production focused with a commitment to client success through a balance of quality, prioritization, creativity and efficiency. Responsibilities: • Ability to work in a collaborative environment and communicate effectively to other members of the team both verbally and in written documentation • Develop using the latest client-side web technologies, specifically HTML5, CSS and JavaScript (jQuery) • Remain current on new technologies and design trends for web, mobile and social media platforms • Collaborate with design, development and client services teams to maintain creative and efficient production processes • Assist in the estimating and scoping process for new work • Maintain and contribute to coding standards to promote best practices and community building both internally and externally • Recommend timely, researched, high-quality solutions and services to clients to further business objectives • Suggest areas for improvement in internal processes, along with possible solutions • Able to work in Brooklyn, NY or Chapel Hill, NC These attributes are pretty essential: • Understands the application of and demonstrates expert knowledge of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript • Possesses excellent working knowledge of the Adobe Creative Suite, specifically Photoshop • Thrives in a team environment and facilitates effective team interaction • Familiar with source control principles and comfortable with Git • Experience with coding and deploying applications in a cross-platform and cross-browser environment • Experience with CMS integration and maintenance, especially Drupal • Experience with MVC frameworks such as Yii, Rails, Symphony and CodeIgniter • Experience with PHP, Ruby and other Web programming languages • Familiar with integrating websites and web applications with social media platforms and third party APIs – Ashe Avenue loves you. Ashe Avenue Facebook Twitter LinkedIn Brooklyn 67 West St. Floor 4 (Greendesk, #C6) Brooklyn, NY 11222 Chapel Hill 1506 E Franklin St. Suite 300 Chapel Hill, NC 27514 Stay in the Loop Sign up for the latest news from Ashe Avenue. ©2014 Ashe Avenue Development, LLC", is_draft: true, company_id: 76, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, key_skill_one: "JS/HTML/CSS", key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/senior-javascript-engineer", title: "Senior Javascript Engineer", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions Senior Javascript Engineer New York, NY MongoDB is seeking an experienced Javascript engineer to lead user interface development for our Server Web Administration tool. You will be responsible for UI design and implementation for the MongoDB Web Administration tool and serving as an advocate for users of this product throughout the design and development process.Responsibilities Work with the MongoDB UX team to design the user interface for the MongDB Server Administration tool Evaluate frameworks and technologies used Lead implemention and test of tool features Work in a small team environment that will directly impact the global engineering community Requirements 3+ years developing client side web applications Experience with modern front-end technologies HTML5, AJAX, CORS, Bootstrap, CSS a plus! Strong experience working with JavaScript frameworks and the ability to evaluate and explain the benefits and tradeoffs of multiple frameworks Experience working with version control systems, specifically git Nice to haves You consider yourself an expert level developer You have good web design chops You're flexible. You'll be joining a small team, so you're willing to take on a wide variety of responsibilities You are well organized, used to juggling many tasks at once You realize that comprehensive testing is your responsibility as a developer Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading NoSQL database. Designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable. MongoDB enables new types of applications, better customer experience, faster time to market and lower costs. MongoDB has a thriving global community with more than 6 million downloads, 125,000 Online Education registrations, 25,000 MongoDB User Group (MUG) members and 20,000 annual MongoDB Days attendees. The company has more than 900 customers, including many of the world’s largest organizations. To all recruitment agencies: MongoDB does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias or MongoDB employees. MongoDB is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Life @ MongoDB 1 2 Did You Know? You can apply for a job using your LinkedIn account! Save time and include added resources by using LinkedIn to include your resume, work experience, and recommendations in your application. Apply Now With LinkedIn Apply now in New York, NY Copyright © 2014 MongoDB, Inc. Legal Notices Information you submit as part of your application is subject to the MongoDB Jobs Privacy Policy", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, key_skill_one: "Javascript", key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil},
  {link: "http://betaworks.com/job/dots-vp-of-engineering/", title: "Dots – Head of Engineering", full_text: "betaworks - a company of builders Purpose Products People Community < Back to Studio Positions Dots – Head of Engineering Apply Now We’re adding millions of new players to Dots each month. With this scale comes new and interesting challenges on how to efficiently organize and process profile and leaderboard data. In addition to data, we’re building a creative and talented engineering team in need of a strong technical leader. Our ideal candidate is as creative as they are process-driven, and knows how to get the best out of a strong team. We’re not stuck to any specific technologies, but we’re currently using Cocos2D, PHP, MySQL, Apportable SDK (for Android), with our API scaled on multiple Amazon EC2 machines. Responsibilities: Provide strategic direction of technical, architectural and design efforts Build and organize growing team with technical disciplines Manage delivery of multiple and concurrent product releases Build, maintain, and evangelize technology best practices across organization Create dev operations infrastructure and process to support rapid growth Deep understanding of industry trends and emerging technologies Work with product team to build a strong quality assurance practice that includes manual and automated testing Personally own a specific technical function as an active developer (iOS, infrastructure, or API) Qualifications: 3 years of technical management and development experience Desire and passion for pushing the bounds of latest technologies Experience with Agile/Scrum/Lean principles and values Experience building scalable solutions for handling high volume traffic Strong communication, analytical and presentation skills Deep subject matter expertise of a specific technical function (infrastructure, backend development, frontend web or mobile development, etc) Apply Now Open Beta Privacy Policy User Agreement Events Jobs Blog 