  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/systems-engineer", title: "Systems Engineer", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions Systems Engineer New York, NY You are a hard-core kernel tweaker and optimizer, scripter and orchestration wizard, network, security, and storage infrastructure specialist. Your job will be to work closely with the core engineering team to develop best practices, validate & optimize infrastructure configurations, develop automation and help our customers build and engineer state of the art MongoDB deployments. You must have direct hands on experience operating modern high scale web based applications.Responsibilities Develop best practices for deployment (e.g. HA, DR) and maintenance (e.g. expanding file-system, cluster recovery etc.) Understand the performance impact of kernel configurations, BIOS settings, NIC/HBA/RAID setup Understand where and how to scale Assist engineering triaging customers deployments, performance issues, debugging the full application life cycle Maintain linux packages and recipes for automated installers (chef,puppet) Document and/or provide input to documentation and white papers Requirements 5-7 years of system administration or development operations Day-to-Day management of a production cluster of 50+ nodes Familiarity with scripting languages (Python, JavaScript, Perl) and with MongoDB a big plus Excellent analytical skills Excellent verbal and written skills BSc in Computer Science Nice to Haves You want to be part of a great team building the most significant database innovation in decades You consider yourself an expert level administration \"geek\", build your own kernels and want to expand your knowledge You're flexible, joining a small team, so you're willing to take on a wide variety of responsibilities You are well organized, used to keeping many balls in the air at the same time Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from h