  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/technical-writer-documentation-specialist", title: "Technical Writer, Documentation Specialist", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions Technical Writer, Documentation Specialist New York, NY You want to help us develop the best technical documentation, tutorials, reference materials, and educational materials possible to support the MongoDB and its users.Responsibilities Work as a part of the engineering team to document new features and products Develop and maintain new documentation and other technical materials to support users of MongoDB Organize complex information in easy to understand documents, tutorials, and reference material Review and edit documentation and specifications from other engineers and Technical Writers Requirements Flexiblity. You are comfortable joining a small team, where you'll be responsible for writing and maintaining documentation for a variety of products and services to support many different kinds of users Experience writing clear and concise technical documentation for complex topics Experience organizing, structuring, and maintaining large bodies of documentation Familiarity with systems software (e.g. Unix/Linux, Databases) as well as web development tools and practices Ability to read, understand, and communicate the function and behavior of code Excellent analytic and problem solving skills Excellent verbal and written communication skills You're technically inclined and curious, and are comfortable working closely with, and understanding the language and concerns of, database kernel engineers, administrators, and application developers You're interested in databases, software development, and open source are great and want to contribute to these kinds of projects You want to contribute to building great open source database software Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data m