  {link: "http://www.asheavenue.com/careers/", title: "Back-End Developer", full_text: "Ashe Avenue Contact Blog Careers Services Team Work Careers Back-End Developer Ashe Avenue is searching for an adventurous spirit to join our development team. Do you enjoy experimenting with new technologies? Do you enjoy contributing to the open-source world? Do you find optimization, caching, server architecture, and object-oriented or MVC programming enjoyable? While we typically shun labels, we are looking for a back-end team member with a passion for server-side development. You must possess a feverish desire to produce top quality, D.R.Y. code. You must be comfortable working in a fast-paced environment and wired to research and look for the newest tools, technologies or libraries. You must enjoy jumping between languages, environments and projects while never letting your skills stagnate. You will be working with skilled developers across our Brooklyn and Chapel Hill offices, and collaborate with members of the front-end team to produce high-profile, client-facing work. We have offices in Brooklyn, NY and Chapel Hill, NC so the candidate should live in either of those areas. Please send your resume to jobs [at] asheavenue.com, and be sure to include your GitHub page or links to work you’ve done. Requirements: At least 2 years developing professionally in Ruby, PHP, or server-side Javascript, plus a desire to continually add to your language portfolio Strong understanding and experience with web application frameworks like Rails, Yii, Cake, or Express, etc. Comfort with modern databases, either Postgres, MySQL, or any of the various NoSQL databases (Mongo, Rethink, Couch, etc.) A preference for developing in an agency, consulting, or startup environment Natural curiosity, hunger, and a desire to progress through fast-paced client work Experience with native mobile application development for iOS or Android is preferred but not required. Comfortable working in Linux environments Experience working with Git Nice-to-haves: DevOps or sysadmin experience Experience with native mobile application development for iOS or Android Open-source contributions We offer full health benefits, 401k plans, and employee incentive programs. We love technology, music, and art. We could be your new home. Drop us a line. Seriously. jobs [at] asheavenue.com. Front-End Developer Ashe Avenue is looking for an experienced Front-end Developer responsible for producing HTML markup, CSS and client-side engineering solutions for websites and web applications. The position requires extensive knowledge and understanding of HTML, CSS and JavaScript. This role is production focused with a commitment to client success through a balance of quality, prioritization, creativity and efficiency. Responsibilities: • Ability to work in a collaborative environment and communicate effectively to other members of the team both verbally and in written documentation • Develop using the latest client-side web technologies, specifically HTML5, CSS and JavaScript (jQuery) • Remain current on new technologies and design trends for web, mobile and social media platforms • Collaborate with design, development and client services teams to maintain creative and efficient production processes • Assist in the estimating and scoping process for new work • Maintain and contribute to coding standards to promote best practices and community building both internally and externally • Recommend timely, researched, high-quality solutions and services to clients to further business objectives • Suggest areas for improvement in internal processes, along with possible solutions • Able to work in Brooklyn, NY or Chapel Hill, NC These attributes are pretty essential: • Understands the application of and demonstrates expert knowledge of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript • Possesses excellent working knowledge of the Adobe Creative Suite, specifically Photoshop • Thrives in a team environment and facilitates effective team interaction • Familiar with source control principles and comfortable with Git • Experience with coding and deploying applications in a cross-platform and cross-browser environment • Experience with CMS integration and maintenance, especially Drupal • Experience with MVC frameworks such as Yii, Rails, Symphony and CodeIgniter • Experience with PHP, Ruby and other Web programming languages • Familiar with integrating websites and web applications with social media platforms and third party APIs – Ashe Avenue loves you. Ashe Avenue Facebook Twitter LinkedIn Brooklyn 67 West St. Floor 4 (Greendesk, #C6) Brooklyn, NY 11222 Chapel Hill 1506 E Franklin St. Suite 300 Chapel Hill, NC 27514 Stay in the Loop Sign up for the latest news from Ashe Avenue. ©2014 Ashe Avenue Development, LLC", is_draft: true, company_id: 76, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, key_skill_one: "Rails", key_skill_two: "PHP", sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/lead-software-engineer-test", title: "Lead Software Engineer in Test", full_text: "Skip to main content Careers Menu Careers Home Positions Our Culture Back to Positions Lead Software Engineer in Test New York, NY You want to build, lead and mentor an organization creating the infrastructure, tools, frameworks and test cases to validate the correctness and acceptability of the MongoDB databases and Management Service (MMS). Leading a cross-functional team you need to build reliable mechanisms (automation frameworks, fault-injection, simulation, etc.) to test a distributed database at scale, not just in terms of numbers of nodes, but data volume, throughput, response time etc. Our customers and community value reliability and consistency, so test cases will need to be design with the engineering and product management teams combined with your wild imagination to push the edges and boundaries of the product with the goal of Customer Success. You need to be both a visionary and and effective leader, mentor and manager of people. Responsibilities Architect, Design & Implement frameworks, tools and other building blocks to test the products Effectively leads a team of engineers to build the testing infrastructure and test cases to ensure the correctness, acceptance and performance Work with engineers to perform root-cause analysis and preliminary problem diagnosis Work with MongoDB users and customers to reproduce bug reports from the field Work with the product manager and engineering leads to produce great test plans and ensure that they are completed Juggle priorities and plans in order to make the date Manage, mentor and grow the test team and test function within the engineering organization Provide the tooling for engineers to provide \"early warning\" of degradations in quality (in a sandbox or in the mainline code) Requirements 8+ years leading and/or managing an engineering team Excellent Programming knowledge of (C or C++ preferred, Java / Scala ok) Excellent scripting skills (Shell, JavaScript, Python or Go) Experience testing distributed & enterprise software Excellent verbal & written communication skills Strong UNIX/Linux operational skills (Windows a bonus) Strong problem-solving skills Should have experience with cloud providers (Amazon EC2, Azure, Joyent , Rackspace, Softlayer) Should have database experience (SQL or Non-relational) Should have experience with/knowledge of hypervisor technologies (KVM, VMWare, Xen or Hyper-V) Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading NoSQL database. Designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable. MongoDB enables new types of applications, better customer experience, faster time to market and lower costs. MongoDB has a thriving global community with more than 6 million downloads, 125,000 Online Education registrations, 25,000 MongoDB User Group (MUG) members and 20,000 annual MongoDB Days attendees. The company has more than 900 customers, including many of the world’s largest organizations. To all recruitment agencies: MongoDB does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias or MongoDB employees. MongoDB is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Life @ MongoDB 1 2 Did You Know? You can apply for a job using your LinkedIn account! Save time and include added resources by using LinkedIn to include your resume, work experience, and recommendations in your application. Apply Now With LinkedIn Apply now in New York, NY Copyright © 2014 MongoDB, Inc. Legal Notices Information you submit as part of your application is subject to the MongoDB Jobs Privacy Policy", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 8, key_skill_one: "C/C++", key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Testing", description: nil},
  {link: "http://betaworks.com/job/dots-mobile-engineer-2-openings/", title: "Dots – Mobile Engineer", full_text: "betaworks - a company of builders Purpose Products People Community < Back to Studio Positions Dots – Mobile Engineer (2 openings) Apply Now We’re building more games! We’re scaling our team and titles (games) in pairs of two. Each title has a game designer paired with a mobile engineer. Our game designers know how to code and prototype, but are often self-taught and spend more time thinking about game mechanic, design, and user experience, so they work best when paired with a ridiculously talented and creative mobile engineer. You’ll enjoy working with our team on the entire design process and get to focus on what you do best — building apps. Responsibilities Work with your game designer to turn a concept in high-quality mobile app Write beautiful self-documenting code that others can easily read and adapt Participate in regular code reviews Communicate iOS project status to team in an accurate and detailed way Work with peer teams to share best practices and help out as needed Qualifications 2 years experience in iOS development 6 months experience in Cocos2D development Proficient in C and Objective-C Self-reliant hacker that can quickly adopt new systems and languages Strong communicator with excellent problem solving skills Apply Now Open Beta Privacy Policy User Agreement Events Jobs Blog Facebook Twitter © 2014 betaworks 416 W 13th Suite 203 New York NY 10014 Made in NY.", is_draft: true, company_id: 101, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, key_skill_one: "IOS", key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Mobile", description: nil},
