  {link: "http://www.ahalife.com/jobs#", title: "DevOps Engineer", full_text: "FREE US SHIPPING NEW MEMBERS RECEIVE $20 CREDIT ON FIRST ORDER OVER $100 Member Benefits &plus;− FREE US SHIPPING NEW MEMBERS RECEIVE $20 CREDIT ON FIRST ORDER OVER $100 details AHALife Shop Discover Brands Curators About CANCEL » sign in my bag New Best Sellers Gifts Women Men Kids Beauty Home Dining Tech Experiences WE'RE HIRING AHAlife connects the best the world has to offer to the most discerning individuals from around the globe. We are revolutionizing the way brands and publishers engage with consumers by integrating the art of storytelling, commerce and social curation. Our mission is to allow consumers to discover the most inspiring content and products that help them live their lives to the fullest. Founded in September 2010 by MIT engineer-turned commerce and media industry expert Shauna Mei, the company has grown quickly to over 40 employees. Investors include First Mark Capital, DCM, and Rakuten, board members include Deepak Chopra and former chairman of LVMH, Renaud Dutreil. Curators include industry experts such as Tim Gunn, chef Daniel Boulud, filmmaker Wendi Murdoch, model Iman, and designer Donna Karan. AHAlife was recently named by Fast Company Magazine as one of the 50 Most Innovative Companies in the World of 2013. Check out our recent press. Due to the large volume of applications, we are only able to respond to those who have been selected for interviews. All positions are for our office on Bond Street in Manhattan, New York. OPEN POSITIONS About Press Jobs Contact Us Help Terms of Use Privacy Policy Gift Cards FOLLOW US Copyright © 2013 AHAlife Inc. All rights reserved. top", is_draft: true, company_id: 36, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, key_skill_one: "Unix", key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Dev Ops", description: nil},
  {link: "https://adstruc.com/s/home/jobs/engineer", title: "Software Engineer", full_text: "Login Forgot your password? Login I am a: Agency Advertiser Operator « Back to jobs Software Engineer Location: NYC Department: Engineering Type: Full Time We Are Looking For: ADstruc seeks an experienced software engineer to join its software engineering team and help us build the best outdoor media-buying platform in the industry Responsibilities: Design, architect, build and maintain ADstruc media-buying platform Work on everything from backend and user interface to database systems and third-party integrations Regardless of which area of the product you work on, we want your involvement in designing, coding and testing the application Requirements: 2-4 years of software engineering experience in a startup environment Experience developing web applications as part of a team with agile methodologies Excellent coding, design, and architectural skills (PHP, SQL, Linux) Strong interpersonal communication skills A college degree from a Computer Science program You should be able to work daily in our New York office Benefits: Apple equipment Competitive salary Health, dental and vision insurance Stock options Team outings, including volunteering at various charities Great SoHo office space Free ping pong lessons We Are: ADstruc is the leading buying platform for the outdoor advertising industry, including both traditional and digital Out-of-Home media. With an emphasis on data-driven planning, ADstruc's platform helps agencies, national brands, and local businesses discover and efficiently purchase Out-of-Home media across hundreds of operators. Our cloud-based solution also allows outdoor advertising operators to easily manage and promote their inventory online and interact with clients in real-time. Our entire team is based in Soho and we are backed by some of the biggest names in venture capital, including DFJ, RRE, SoftTech, Founder Collective and more. Apply for this posit