  {link: "https://arc90.recruiterbox.com/jobs/28598/", title: "Director of IT Infrastructure", full_text: "Employer Login Arc90 Jobs Director of IT Infrastructure New York, New York, United States SFX Entertainment requires an experienced IT professional to oversee all aspects of its IT infrastructure needs in its 5 New York area offices. The ideal candidate for this position is able to deftly design, plan, coordinate,manage and execute IT projects and activities in a collaborative and effective manner. Areas of Responsibility Wireless and wired networks Internet connection service Video and voice telecom systems Device support (“help desk”) This role does not include oversight of any other communication or collaboration tools, services, or technologies. In other words, the focus is on the physical IT infrastructure of the business, not the application layer. Capabilities & Responsibilities: Ability to articulate and establish IT departmental goals, objectives, operatingprocedures and best practices Ability to communicate these to staff and management team, and connect these to business practices Communicate IT progress and achievements in terms that non-technical staff can understand Provide device support (hardware and OS) to 100+ users across 5 offices — including Windows, Mac, iOS, and Android devices, and printers Support LAN and WAN network including routers, VPN, firewalls. Manage company voice and video telecommunications, video conferencing and A/V related office equipment and services Expertly handle vendor relations, contract management, SLAs, renewals. etc... Facility with Budgeting and Scoping Requirements: Strong technical knowledge of networks and operating systems Strong technical knowledge of current network hardware, protocols, and standards especially with Cisco routers and ASAs Strong and proven project management skills Strong consensus/relationship building and communications skills Experience with data back-up and disaster recovery solutions Proven experience in IT infrastructure planning and development 3+ years of IT experience and 1+ years of management skills About Us: Arc90 is part of the SFX family of companies. We are a team of designers, developers, and strategists dedicated to building the next generation of electronic music experiences. We offer a relaxed and fun work environment where your input and abilities will have a direct impact on the end product of every project you are a part of. You’ll be part of a tight-knit, supportive, creative, collaborative community that is passionate about building great user experiences, learning new skills and techniques, and doing the right thing. Join us! To Apply: Please send us a short note that explains why you'd be a uniquely good fit for this role. Apply for this position or See other jobs at Arc90 Application Form First Name * Last Name Email * Phone * Resume * Cover Letter * Twitter Handle Website / Blog / Portfolio Tell your friends about this position In October 2013, Arc90 was acquired by SFX Entertaiment. We're continuing to do the same great product work we've always done, but now we're applying our skills to create an exciting new music platform. You can read about the announcement on our blog. Why Work at Arc90/SFX? Arc90 is part of the SFX family of companies. We are a team of designers, developers, and strategists dedicated to building the next generation of electronic music experiences. We offer a relaxed and fun work environment where your input and abilities will have a direct impact on the end product of every project you are a part of. You’ll be part of a tight-knit, supportive, creative, collaborative community that is passionate about building great user experiences, learning new skills and techniques, and doing the right thing. Perks The opportunity to work with new and emerging technologies. A flexible schedule in terms of work hours and location. An environment that prides itself on pragmatism and collaboration. If you have the right answer, we listen. An Employee Development Program, including a budget for conferences and classes. Creative outlets for side projects, including hackathons and lab days. A team that is always helping one another – someone almost always has the answer for any question you’ve got. Kick-ass parties. Weekly company lunch. More positions at Arc90 Mobile App Developer to design and build a new music platform Front End Web Developer to design and build a new music platform Java Developer to design and build a new music platform and 2 more jobs powered byRecruiterbox", is_draft: true, company_id: 66, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, key_skill_one: nil, key_skill_two: nil, sub_dept: "Executive", description: nil},
  {link: "https://www.smartrecruiters.com/AppboyInc/74187403-web-software-developer", title: "WEB SOFTWARE DEVELOPER", full_text: "Web Software Developer New York, NY Company Description Appboy is a rapidly growing analytics and marketing automation platform for mobile apps. Job Description Appboy is looking for a web developer to help build and maintain our many online assets, including our website, blog, documentation sites, and more. You'll work closely with our Success Squad and Marketing teams to enhance the public face of Appboy and create a first class experience for our clients. We use a diverse technology stack across our online presence. Candidates should have previous experience with software and product design, be able to intelligently discuss their design decisions, and a passion for getting things done. Since this role will entail working closely with different stakeholders on a wide variety of technologies, excellent communication skills and the ability to rapidly learn new technologies are also a must. ResponsibilitiesContribute to Appboy's public-facing websites and web assets (landing pages, etc.).Work closely with our Marketing and Success Squad teams to enhance Appboy's client-facing sites and provide an excellent experience for our clients.Maintain knowledge freshness and identify feature opportunities and evolving best practices for our web stack. Qualifications Experience with functional languages and MVC frameworks such as Ruby on Rails or Python/Django.Experience with frontend languages and modern web technologies.Strong sense of excellent user experience and an eye for quality design. An ability and willingness to rapidly dive in and use new technologies.(Bonus) Experience with Wordpress or other common blogging / content delivery solutions. Posted by Kevin Wang share this job The free social recruiting platform Learn more", is_draft: true, company_id: 56, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, key_skill_one: "Rails", key_skill_two: "Python", sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil},
